title: I WAS A CONSULTANT ON SAY YES TO THE DRESS!! ðŸ¤
description: Wow. I canâ€™t believe the day has come!!! 4 years ago I moved to New York City from my little hometown in the South, to work as a bridal consultant at Kleinfeld Bridal. Since taking the job my dream was to be a featured consultant on Say Yes to the Dress. As every little girl did, I wanted to be on the show and host with Randy Fenoli. Just a few short months in, that happened! What a whirlwind it was. I have waited and waited for my episode to air and this morning I woke up to my episode on Hulu!! Although I am no longer working in bridal, I will cherish this moment forever ðŸ¤

More About Mark Allan Wolfe

Mark Allan Wolfe (ASCAP) I am a music composer, producer, musician, songwriter, artist, and speaker. I create original custom music for film and Tv.  The primary genres I tend to focus on include Rock, Acoustic, Indie, Blues, Chill / Lounge, Smooth Jazz, Underscore. I also have a wide variety of other genres which include World, Latin, Classical and More
His music has found placement in some of today's hottest shows on television and the web, and has been used by global brands like Unilever, GM, SONY, Coke, Pepsi, ADOBE, Microsoft, and the NFL.

Mark's music has been featured on a variety of network and cable TV channels, including Discovery Networks, Lifetime, HISTORY, NBC, HBO, CBS, ABC, MTV, BRAVO, and Entertainment Studios.
